text: Andrea Kossányiová (born 6 August 1993) is a Czech volleyball player, playing as a Outside spiker. She is part of the Czech Republic women's national volleyball team. She competed at the 2019 Women's European Volleyball League, winning a gold medal. On club level she plays for PVK Olymp Prague, VK Agel Prostejov, VK UP Olomouc, and Volley Wrocław. == References == Category:1993 births Category:Czech volleyball players Category:Living people
